(129, 129, NULL, 3, 'output not XHTML 1.0 valid! w3 validator say''s "48 Errors, 1 warning(s)"...', 'i made some changes at line 146 and 147, so that there are no missing closing tags in the output.\r<br>now the output is XHTML 1.0 valid', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-16 10:30:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/129.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(130, 130, NULL, 3, 'com_installer/manage is loading very slowly', 'When I try to load "administrator/index.php?option=com_installer&view=manage" on my local installation, it is taking too long.\r<br>\r<br>My maximum_execution_time in php.ini was set to 30 seconds and it could never load because of that.\r<br>\r<br>Joomla : 2.5.1\r<br>Server : Win7 pro x64 with XAMP\r<br>PHP version : php 5.3.5', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-16 11:05:39', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(131, 131, NULL, 3, 'less $lang->load() part 0: JLanguage::load() accepts an array of paths', '...to search for language files.\r<br>\r<br>allows a single line of\r<br>```   $lang->load(''plg_''.$folder.''_''.$element, array(JPATH_ADMINISTRATOR,JPATH_PLUGINS.''/''.$folder.''/''.$element), true, false, false);```\r<br>to perform the same as a bulks of\r<br>```   $lang->load(''plg_''.$folder.''_''.$element, JPATH_ADMINISTRATOR, null, false, false)\r<br>|| $lang->load(''plg_''.$folder.''_''.$element, JPATH_PLUGINS.''/''.$folder.''/''.$element, null, false, false)\r<br>|| $lang->load(''plg_''.$folder.''_''.$element, JPATH_ADMINISTRATOR, $lang->getDefault(), false, false)\r<br>|| $lang->load(''plg_''.$folder.''_''.$element, JPATH_PLUGINS.''/''.$folder.''/''.$element, $lang->getDefault(), false, false);```\r<br>\r<br>I''ll add subsequent pull requests where this change is used. \r<br>Next part will handle "tpl_" files.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-19 23:41:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/131.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(132, 132, NULL, 3, 'less $lang->load() part 1: tpl files backend and libraries/joomla/*', 'follow up of https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/131\r<br>uses modified JLanguage::load() to load template language files.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-19 23:46:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/132.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(133, 133, NULL, 3, 'query selects non-template extension elements.', 'Scenario: Let''s say I have a template ''atomic'' and a set of 2 plugins (authentication/atomic, user/atomic).\r<br>Going to ``Extensions > Template Manager > Styles`` shows up 2 additional styles for ''atomic'' template (which in fact are plugins with same name).\r<br>\r<br>this appeared after migration 1.7 > 2.5 probably due to restructured query\r<br>\r<br>duplicate of #93', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-21 14:28:53', '2012-02-21 14:31:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/133.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(134, 134, NULL, 3, 'The constants IS_WIN, IS_MAC, IS_UNIX are used in the system?', 'Checking the file [libraries/import.php](https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master/libraries/import.php#L22)  I''m  a question regarding the use of constants **IS_WIN**, **IS_MAC**, **IS_UNIX**.\r<br>\r<br>Somewhere in the CMS are used?\r<br>\r<br>Moreover [libraries/joomla/filesystem/path.php](https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master/libraries/joomla/filesystem/path.php#L13)  file defines constants: JPATH_ISWIN and JPATH_ISMAC on lines 13, 16 respectively.\r<br>\r<br>The file [./libraries/joomla/application/application.php](https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master//libraries/joomla/application/application.php#L1184) define function ''isWinOS''\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>The object **JFTP** [in its constructor](https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master/libraries/joomla/client/ftp.php#L157) sets the variable **OS**.\r<br>\r<br>All these files make use of the form:\r<br>\r<br>```php\r<br><?php\r<br>substr(PHP_OS, 0, 3)\r<br>\r<br>```\r<br>to determine the operating system.\r<br>\r<br>the external libraries for example:  **phpmailer** and **geshi** also make use of this form.\r<br>\r<br>IMHO is necessary to define these variables.\r<br>\r<br>However appear in the documentation. <https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/blob/staging/docs/manual/en-US/chapters/introduction.xml#L41>\r<br>\r<br>Personally I consider that:\r<br>\r<br>1. - These constants should not exist.\r<br>\r<br>2. - Or if the file ''iasf.php'' is loaded before the other files, then you should make use of these constants.\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Personally I think it''s the first best solution(educes the learning curve of the framework).\r<br>\r<br>P. S. I would like to help review this detail.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-22 06:34:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(135, 135, NULL, 3, 'get rid of Notice ''Only variable references should be returned by reference''', 'php 5+, tested on php 5.3.0', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-22 13:08:03', '2012-02-24 16:04:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/135.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
