(141, 141, NULL, 3, 'ContentBuildRoute does not remove layout if link attached to menu item', 'In components/com_content/router.php, the following condition (line 47) does not remove the layout from the query : \r<br>\r<br><pre>\r<br>// are we dealing with an article or category that is attached to a menu item?\r<br>if (($menuItem instanceof stdClass) && $menuItem->query[''view''] == $query[''view''] && isset($query[''id'']) && $menuItem->query[''id''] == intval($query[''id''])) {\r<br>		unset($query[''view'']);\r<br>\r<br>		if (isset($query[''catid''])) {\r<br>			unset($query[''catid'']);\r<br>		}\r<br>\r<br>		unset($query[''id'']);\r<br>\r<br>		return $segments;\r<br>	}\r<br></pre>\r<br>\r<br>this may result in links like index.php/extensions?layout=blog, where the original link was something like index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=20&Itemid=527\r<br>\r<br>Easily fixed by removing the layout from the $query, eg:\r<br>\r<br><pre>\r<br>// are we dealing with an article or category that is attached to a menu item?\r<br>if (($menuItem instanceof stdClass) && $menuItem->query[''view''] == $query[''view''] && isset($query[''id'']) && $menuItem->query[''id''] == intval($query[''id''])) {\r<br>		unset($query[''view'']);\r<br>\r<br>		if (isset($query[''catid''])) {\r<br>			unset($query[''catid'']);\r<br>		}\r<br>		\r<br>		if (isset($query[''layout''])) {\r<br>			unset($query[''layout'']);\r<br>		}\r<br>\r<br>		unset($query[''id'']);\r<br>\r<br>		return $segments;\r<br>	}\r<br></pre>\r<br>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-28 14:12:30', '2012-02-28 14:41:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(142, 142, NULL, 3, 'ContentBuildRoute does not remove layout if link attached to menu item', 'In components/com_content/router.php the layout is not removed from the query if the link is attached to a menu item.\r<br>\r<br>This may result in links like index.php/extensions?layout=blog, where the original link was something like index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=20&Itemid=527', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-28 14:37:02', '2012-03-02 08:45:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/142.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(143, 143, 28149, 3, '[#28149] ImageManager Javascript Error', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28149\r<br>\r<br>The content of the onchange tag of #folderlist (as shown in Firebug) was:\r<br>\r<br>ImageManager.setFolder(this.options[this.selectedIndex].value, \r<br>\r<br>which throws an syntax error. Subsequently, the folder view doesn''t change.\r<br>\r<br>I removed the quotes as the variables are filtered as integer, anyway.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-29 08:16:59', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/143.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(144, 144, NULL, 3, 'Removed reference to JTree and JNode from menu module in backend', 'I have a pull request (#677) running on the platform that deprecates JNode and JTree, two broken classes that are (almost) nowhere used. Except for the backend menu of the CMS. This pull request removes the reference in the backend module to that class. If at some point a proper implementation of JNode and JTree are implemented, the module could be rewritten to use those. For the moment it''s best to just copy that code over.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-03-01 13:25:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/144.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
