(184, 184, NULL, 3, 'Make Atomic more usable.', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-09 19:52:25', '2012-07-06 15:43:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/184.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(185, 185, NULL, 3, 'SQL92 RDBMS Portability', 'First set of patches to assist RDBMS portability as previously discussed on the general development list. This covers the following:\r<br>\r<br> - Identifier quoting of SQL reserved words:\r<br>    - LANGUAGE\r<br>    - MODULE\r<br>    - OPTION\r<br>    - TIME\r<br>\r<br> - Identifier quoting of Virtuoso reserved word:\r<br>    - PASSWORD\r<br>\r<br> - Quoting of string literals in some places\r<br>\r<br> - Correct use of non-standard != logic comparison operator to <> \r<br>\r<br> - Casting of some long types used in SQL functions that may not support long types\r<br>\r<br>These changes are organised by front/admin then by component/module/plugin but squashed into single commits with respect to the categories of changes listed above. Given that none of the categories of changes are intended to alter any functional features, I hope that this is suitably divided and correct granularity for manual testing.\r<br>\r<br>If preferred the commits are available unsquashed on separate branches under wdaniels/joomla-cms as indicated by the [branch-name] prefixes of the squashed commits messages where merged into this (sql92) branch.\r<br>\r<br>These patches are relatively trivial and I do not believe to be contentious. Further patch sets I intend to raise for discussion on joomla platform/cms lists as appropriate.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-10 12:06:16', '2012-04-25 12:20:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/185.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(186, 186, NULL, 3, 'Updater for extensions', 'Hi\r<br>\r<br>In libraries/joomla/updater/adaptors/extension.php on line 46 & 47 you will find the following two lines:\r<br>\r<br>$this->current_update->folder = "";\r<br>$this->current_update->client_id = 1;\r<br>\r<br>These bascially hardcode the updater to look for extensions that have a client_id of 1 and no folder. The problem here is that it effectively blocks updates for any extension that uses a client_id of 0 (site templates, libraries, plugins and modules) and any that use folders (plugins).\r<br>\r<br>I am not familiar enough with this area of the Joomla code but a have had a look around it seems the best solution would be too include these in the update manifest using <clientid /> and <folder /> tags. If they are not specified it can set these defaults to ensure backwards compatibility while allowing those who need it to get these updates working.\r<br>\r<br>This code appears to have come out of this discussion: https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/joomla-dev-general/R4g0-Q2pWXk/SmLaJEsTUK0J where the suggested clumsy alternative seems the better option?\r<br>\r<br>I am happy to make these changes and provide a patch unless someone has a better suggestion?\r<br>\r<br>Thanks\r<br>Dave\r<br>\r<br>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-10 15:56:25', '2012-04-10 16:55:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187, 187, NULL, 3, 'Tag new platform versions', 'It would help me quite a bit if tags could be added at fixed commits when new platform changes are brought over.   IE 11.2  full, 11.3 partial, 12.1 full, etc\r<br>\r<br>I often compare branches between my local site, the cms, and the platform to see whats new and whether I want to integrate it early or not.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-11 09:59:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188, 188, NULL, 3, 'Using remember me on com_users login', 'Currently there isn''t any use of remember me on com_users login', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-11 18:12:13', '2012-04-28 06:29:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/188.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(189, 189, NULL, 3, 'Stop default handling of href in toolbar buttons', 'This will  make it possible to utilize the toolbar buttons in the frontend if the template specifies the <base> tag. With the current implementation, when the base tag is in effect it will navigate away from the page when toolbar buttons are clicked since it interprets href="#" relative to the base and disregards the query string.\r<br>\r<br>For example, if I have a toolbar in index.php?option=com_foobar the href="#" attribute will refer to "index.php#" which will cause the browser to use the link and navigate away from the page using a GET as it is interpreted as a different page instead of submitting the form using Joomla.submitbutton(''task''); and using a POST.\r<br>\r<br>Without the <base> tag this is not an issue as  the href="#" attribute will refer to "index.php?option=com_foobar#" and the browser will recognize it as the "current" page.\r<br>\r<br>So far i''ve found two possible solution to this to I just picked the one which I think is more clear.\r<br>\r<br>```html\r<br><a href="#" onclick="$doTask; return false;">\r<br><a href="#" onclick="event.preventDefault(); $doTask;">\r<br>```\r<br>\r<br>Below is the example code used to generate the toolbar\r<br>\r<br>```php\r<br><?php\r<br>jimport(''joomla.html.toolbar'');\r<br>$bar = JToolBar::getInstance(''toolbar'');\r<br>$bar->appendButton(''Standard'', ''new'',  ''New'',  ''new'',  false);\r<br>?>\r<br>```\r<br>```html\r<br><form action="index.php?option=com_foobar" id="adminForm" name="adminForm" method="post">\r<br>        <div id="toolbar-box">\r<br>                <?php echo $bar->render(); ?>\r<br>        </div>\r<br>        <input type="hidden" name="task" value="" />\r<br></form>\r<br>```', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-12 18:57:05', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/189.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(190, 190, 28403, 3, '[#28403] Validation error on com_finder', 'See http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28403', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-13 06:52:53', '2012-09-17 14:03:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/190.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(191, 191, NULL, 3, 'Updated prepareContent, moved $conflicts to the parameters ', 'Ran into a case where other plugins where causing problems in prepareContent.  In order to work around this, I had to duplicate the entire prepareContent method in my plugin in order to change the list of excluded plugins.  As a proposed solution, I''ve moved the $conflicts array to the parameters for prepareContent.  If not given, it defaults to what it was before, if given it overrides it and allows different plugins to be excluded.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-13 11:57:56', '2012-04-13 18:59:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/191.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(192, 192, NULL, 3, 'Add jpeg support for PHP < 5.3 in Jimage', 'We currently cannot use JImage with jpeg images if PHP < 5.3, so I added the support for previous PHP version.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-17 13:24:00', '2012-04-17 14:15:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/192.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(193, 193, NULL, 3, 'JController::factory() and createEnvironmentArray() as discussed in joomla-dev-cms group', 'Added to JController the following methods:\r<br>\r<br>1) factory()\r<br>2) createEnvironmentArray()\r<br>3) setTask($task)\r<br>\r<br>Changed execute($task) that if no task is passed, it executes the\r<br>$this->task (which is set also by the factory method)\r<br>\r<br>See discussion https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/joomla-dev-cms/7tjVkzc08Ks (Object oriented components , any plan?)\r<br>\r<br>2012-04-19 by Duccio Gasparri <duccio.gasparri@gmail.com>\r<br>Change-Id: I2a4ded062856670e364128f3cb74716b84b23eea', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-19 13:27:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/193.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(194, 194, NULL, 3, 'Changed executeComponent() to use the factory method of JController (see pull request #193 )', 'Changed executeComponent() to use the factory method of JController. The parameter $baseClass is added, and passed by renderComponent().\r<br>\r<br>See discussion "Object oriented components , any plan?"\r<br>https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/joomla-dev-cms/7tjVkzc08Ks\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Change-Id: Ie19778dddc492814dc549c54f1a7c45cf80404c3', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-19 13:37:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/194.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(195, 195, NULL, 3, 'JDatabaseMySQLi::query: 1064 error after update from 1.7', 'One of my own component (business directory) ran perfectly on 1.7 and \r<br>after updating to 2.5 it throws the following error referring to an SQL \r<br>query:\r<br>\r<br>JDatabaseMySQLi::query: 1064 - You have an error in your SQL syntax; check \r<br>the manual that corresponds to your MySQL server version for the right \r<br>syntax to use near '''' at line 1 SQL=SELECT #__bd_packages.picture_num \r<br> FROM #__bd_businesses LEFT JOIN #__bd_packages ON \r<br>#__bd_packages.id=#__bd_businesses.package_id WHERE #__bd_businesses.id=\r<br>\r<br>Call stack\r<br># Function Location\r<br>1 JAdministrator->dispatch() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/index.php:46\r<br>2 JComponentHelper::renderComponent() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/includes/application.php:152\r<br>3 JComponentHelper::executeComponent() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/application/component/helper.php:357\r<br>4 require_once() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/application/component/helper.php:388\r<br>5 JController->execute() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/components/com_businessdirectory/businessdirectory.php:12\r<br>6 BusinessDirectoryController->display() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/application/component/controller.php:754\r<br>7 JController->display() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/components/com_businessdirectory/controller.php:11\r<br>8 BusinessDirectoryViewBusiness->display() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/application/component/controller.php:715\r<br>9 JView->get() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/components/com_businessdirectory/views/business/view.html.php:10\r<br>10 BusinessDirectoryModelBusiness->getForm() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/application/component/view.php:482\r<br>11 JDatabase->loadResult() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/administrator/components/com_businessdirectory/models/business.php:37\r<br>12 JDatabaseMySQLi->query() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/database/database.php:1109\r<br>13 JError::raiseError() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/database/database/mysqli.php:396\r<br>14 JError::raise() /var/www/virtual/domain.com/htdocs/libraries/joomla/error/error.php:251\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>The interesting thing is, that every other query works fine under Joomla \r<br>2.5.\r<br>\r<br>Is there some kind of change in query syntax between 1.7 and 2.5?\r<br>I''m looking for a solution for the problem.\r<br>\r<br>Joomlacode:\r<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28435', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-19 19:57:16', '2012-05-29 19:57:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(196, 196, NULL, 3, 'JComponentHelper::isEnabled returns true if the component doesn''t exist', 'You can see the issue here :\r<br>\r<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28393\r<br>\r<br>JComponentHelper::isEnabled(''com_anycomponent'') will aways return true if the component doesn''t exists because in getComponent($option, $strict = false), $result->enabled was set to true for the default $strict = false value. (logic inversion).\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-04-23 09:19:14', '2012-06-20 12:44:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/196.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(197, 197, NULL, 3, 'Add conversion of "poster" attribute URL in SEF plugin', 'The SEF plugin does not convert the HTML5 poster attribute URL.\r<br>\r<br>This commit adds the "poster" attribute to the regex alongside the "src and "href" attributes.\r<br>\r<br>Tracker - http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=27711', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-25 10:36:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/197.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(198, 198, NULL, 3, 'SQL Portability Patches', 'First set of patches to assist RDBMS portability as previously discussed on the general development list. This covers the following:\r<br>\r<br> - Identifier quoting of SQL reserved words:\r<br>   * LANGUAGE\r<br>   * MODULE\r<br>   * OPTION\r<br>   * TIME\r<br>   * LEVEL\r<br>   * POSITION\r<br>\r<br> - Identifier quoting of Virtuoso (and Oracle) reserved word:\r<br>   * PASSWORD\r<br>\r<br> - Quoting of string literals in some places\r<br>\r<br> - Correct use of non-standard != logic comparison operator to <>\r<br>\r<br> - Casting of some long types used in SQL functions that may not support long types\r<br>\r<br> - Fixed conditional join to categories in weblinks model (mod_weblinks seems to assume the categories table (aliased "c") is always present)\r<br>\r<br> - Fixed duplication of column list in mod_articles_news helper\r<br>\r<br>These changes are organised by front/admin then by component/module/plugin but squashed into single commits with respect to the categories of changes listed above. Given that none of the categories of changes are intended to alter any functional features, I hope that this is suitably divided and correct granularity for manual testing.\r<br>\r<br>If preferred the commits are available unsquashed on separate branches under wdaniels/joomla-cms as indicated by the [branch-name] prefixes of the squashed commits messages where merged into this (sql92) branch.\r<br>\r<br>These patches are relatively trivial and I do not believe to be contentious. Further patch sets I intend to raise for discussion on joomla platform/cms lists as appropriate.\r<br>\r<br>NB: There remains RDBMS portability issues with the use of MySQL DATE_FORMAT function in mod_relateditems and mod_weblinks which require some further investigation. Also issues remain with quoting for the LIKE conditions in mod_relateditems. No doubt other issues also remain; this patch set is not intended to be exhaustive, even with respect to the identified issues.\r<br>\r<br>[JoomlaCode #28391]', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-25 11:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/198.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(199, 199, NULL, 3, 'XHTML: Unescaped Article Title in Category Blog "read more" Links', 'Article category blog layout produces invalid (X)HTML with reserved characters (e.g. ampersand &) not escaped in output of the "read more" link.\r<br>\r<br>[JoomlaCode #28451]', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-25 13:01:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/199.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(200, 200, NULL, 3, 'Check array bounds in menu tree before checking whether menu item is in path', 'The current code generates many non-fatal (but annoying) "Undefined offset" notices. Before checking whether a menu item is in the path, first check whether there is an item at that array index. ', 3, 0, 1, '2012-04-29 23:03:17', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/200.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(201, 201, NULL, 3, 'Notice error with advanced seo and featured articles', 'If you activate the sef_advanced_link option (with a plugin or by temporary hardcode it in the router itself, see line 208) you get a notice error by following this steps:\r<br>\r<br>1. Use an empty Joomla! installation for the best test environment (so other menu links will not "fix" the bug)\r<br>2. Create a com_content article\r<br>3. Set the article as "featured"\r<br>4. Go to the default frontpage home link\r<br>5. Click on the article\r<br>6. Notice: Undefined index: id in components\\com_content\\router.php on line 278\r<br>7. Apply pull request\r<br>8. Check again\r<br>\r<br>Why do you get this notice error?\r<br>Because featured blog links have no "id" as request parameter.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-04 01:14:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/201.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(202, 202, NULL, 3, 'Set the CSS class for JForm field label', 'Related feature tracker item: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8549&tracker_item_id=28450', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-07 03:36:44', '2012-08-29 01:34:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/202.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(203, 203, NULL, 3, 'com_redirect', 'plugin plugins/systems/redirect does not work because an url is searched for the full url;\r<br>it is not found (when a redirect has been created) so a new entry is created, resulting in duplicates', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-08 19:40:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(204, 204, NULL, 3, '#28514 removed duplicated line', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-11 01:46:16', '2012-05-11 08:24:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/204.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(205, 205, NULL, 3, 'Why did they change defines.php', 'Hello,\r<br>\r<br>I installed joomla Joomla! 2.5.4 Stable [ Ember ] 2-April-2012 14:00 GMT on my local server to develop, its a windows machine and the installation is located in a subdirectory of htdocs.\r<br>\r<br>When i put in the $live_site parameter in the configuration script, i cant login anymore, it gives a error page.\r<br>\r<br>I figured out when i replace the forward slashes in administrator/defines.php with directory separators (just like the versions of joomla 1.5) the problem is solved.\r<br>\r<br>Why did they change these files anyway?', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-11 15:02:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(206, 206, NULL, 3, 'Add new MVC classes from the Joomla platform', 'This pull adds the new MVC classes (JControllerBase, JModelBase, JModelDatabase, JViewBase and JViewHtml) from the Joomla Platform without interfaces.  This gives extension developers the option of moving forward with the new concrete class names without generating backward compatibility issues revolving around the reassignment of JController, JModel and JView to interfaces.<br><br>Developers should note carefully that none of these new classes extend from JObject and should use autoloader rules to define where their classes can be found (no more addIncludePath type methods).', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-13 22:27:31', '2012-10-07 22:53:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/206.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(207, 207, NULL, 3, 'missing imports prevent command line installation of extensions', 'Originally described in http://forum.joomla.org/viewtopic.php?f=624&t=716847<br><br>Steps to reproduce:<br><br>1. Download the english language extension from http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/jtranslation1_6/frs/?action=FrsReleaseBrowse&frs_package_id=5651 and unzip to /tmp<br>2. Modify the paths in the following script per your environment and run it<br>3. The installation will fail due to classes failing to autoload<br><br>```php<br>#!/usr/bin/php<br><?php<br>define(''_JEXEC'', 1);<br>define(''JPATH_BASE'', ''/var/www/joomla'');<br>require_once ''configuration.php'';<br>require_once ''includes/defines.php'';<br>require_once ''libraries/import.php'';<br>JInstaller::getInstance()->install(''/tmp/site_en-US'');<br>?><br>```<br>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-14 17:13:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(208, 208, NULL, 3, 'Patch #207', 'Add imports necessary for joomla-cms #207', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-14 17:26:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/208.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(209, 209, NULL, 3, 'CLOSED', 'Too many commits added - please disregard.<br><br>See https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/225', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-14 19:25:52', '2012-06-04 14:02:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/209.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(210, 210, NULL, 3, 'Menu Manager ACL', 'This adds ACL to the menu manager. Most of the code was copied from the content manager. I tried to follow all the conventions in the original code. I hope this helps!', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-16 17:15:52', '2012-05-17 14:11:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/210.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(211, 211, NULL, 3, 'Improved search module', 'Removed repeating classes on the input elements.<br>Put the div (container) on the outside<br><br>More here:<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8103&tracker_item_id=28485', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-18 10:06:06', '2012-06-10 21:17:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/211.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
