(216, 216, NULL, 3, 'Category view only processes content triggers on the first few articles in the list', 'Due to the leading article and intro article usage in the IF statement surrounding the content triggers it results in only the first, for example, 5 articles being processed with triggers. If those triggers are used to alter the authors name for example then only the first 5 will actually change.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-29 12:36:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/216.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(217, 217, NULL, 3, 'Featured view only processes content triggers on the first few articles in the list', 'Due to the leading article and intro article usage in the IF statement surrounding the content triggers it results in only the first, for example, 5 articles being processed with triggers. If those triggers are used to alter the authors name for example then only the first 5 will actually change.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-29 12:38:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/217.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(218, 218, NULL, 3, 'jQuery in Joomla core', 'At J! and Beyond, we discussed ways of implementing jQuery in Joomla 3.0. Here is what we have so far:<br><br>* A minified copy of jQuery 1.7.2<br>* A file with `jQuery.noConflict();`<br>* An additional method for `JHtmlBehavior` (would require Platfrom merge, unless we have a standard way of doing this in the CMS library)<br><br>Calling `JHTML::_(''behavior.jquery'');` loads both jQuery and the separate file with noConflict. This is being done because Joomla currently loads all of the JavaScript files first, then loads all of the JavaScript declarations afterwards. If you load jQuery, then MooTools (or another file that pre-defines `$`), then call `jQuery.noConflict()`, it will not work: http://www.designvsdevelop.com/jquery-in-joomla-i-was-wrong/<br><br>This approach works, but it is sub-optimal as you have to incur the overhead of two HTTP requests. There are two workarounds we could pursue:<br><br>* Manually add `jQuery.noConflict();` at the end of jquery.min.js. We would have to do this every time we update jQuery. This is what WordPress does.<br>* Add new code to `JDocument` and `JDocumentRenderer` that would allow declarations to be added immediately before or after a script is loaded. (I believe @beat mentioned he had a pull request for this on the platform)<br><br>Another thing we may want to consider is adding an option in Joomla that will let you specify a CDN copy of jQuery to use in place of the local one.<br><br>**UPDATE 4 June**: The latest commits now implement code in `JDocument` for "post script" functionality. This allows inline JavaScript to be added immediately after a linked script. These commits also make it possible to specify an alternative path through `JHTML::_(''behavior.jquery'')`. This alternate path can be another copy of jQuery on the server, or the full URL to a CDN copy.<br><br>**UPDATE 18 June**: Prescript functionality has been added, exactly the same as "post script", just before the script loads instead of after. Also, an uncompressed debug copy of jQuery is now available, and is loaded when Joomla is in debug mode.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-31 02:33:30', '2012-09-27 14:55:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/218.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(219, 219, NULL, 3, 'Language in component folder', 'Since joomla 1.7 language files can be put in the language folder inside the component. This was missing in the categories extension when loading extra fields.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-05-31 12:12:22', '2012-06-15 17:21:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/219.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(220, 220, NULL, 3, 'ACL getActions consistency improvements for all components', 'This commit will improve the consistent use of the ACL API across the Joomla components. It also removes the level part of the getActions check for certain components. You want to have all component actions and not just of the specific section, and the component should contain all actions of the other sections of access.xml. Otherwise you might not be able to check for core.manage action to show the permission settings fieldset in an different section for example.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-31 22:37:24', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/220.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(221, 221, NULL, 3, 'Several ACL & Toolbar fixes for com_finder (Smart Search)', 'This patch fixes several ACL and toolbar fixes for com_finder (Smart Search).<br><br>1) Changed position of Option button in toolbar to next to the help button (so it is in line with all other components) for several views<br><br>2) The Index button in the toolbar of Indexed Content view is now only visible when user is allowed for the core.create action instead of visible for user with access to the component.<br><br>3) Purge button visible in toolbar of Indexed Content view when allowed for core.delete instead of core.edit.state (delete action, not a state change)<br><br>4) Clickable state button is now checking for core.edit.state action setting instead of core.manage for several views<br><br>5) The Edit button in the toolbar of the Search Filter view was visible when allowed for the core.create action, now checking for the core.edit action. <br><br>6) "Create a filter" link (visible when no filters added yet) in the Search Filter table now only visible when allowed for the core.create action.<br><br>7) When allowed for core.edit and denied for core.edit.state and editing a Search Filter you were able to change the status (published/unpublished). This is now only possible when allowed for core.edit.state action.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-02 11:12:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/221.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(222, 222, NULL, 3, 'Add option to have no email in feeds. Fix a number of issues in feed vie...', '...ws.<br><br>This is from the following:<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=25295<br><br>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-04 05:05:07', '2012-07-19 12:32:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/222.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(223, 223, NULL, 3, 'Fix Mod_article_news (news flash) so that id does not use LENGTH which', 'is not supported by all databases.<br><br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28526', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-04 12:41:38', '2012-06-07 13:35:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/223.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(224, 224, NULL, 3, 'CLOSED', 'Wrong commit range', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-04 13:52:06', '2012-06-04 14:03:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/224.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(225, 225, NULL, 3, 'Menu Item Alias Should Follow $secure Param of the Item it''s Aliasing', 'In mod_menu, there is no check on an aliased item to see if it''s the menu item it is aliasing is secure or not. The alias should follow the same secure options as it''s the item is is aliasing.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-04 13:59:49', '2012-06-06 08:32:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/225.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(226, 226, NULL, 3, 'Add default for captcha.', 'See<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28449', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-04 22:40:10', '2012-08-09 04:29:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/226.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(227, 227, NULL, 3, 'Bug in Codemirror', '/plugins/editors/codemirror/codemirror.php - line 153<br><br>$styleSheet (meant to be an array) is being set to a string. This will cause the foreach on line 172 to break. <br><br>This bug is unnoticed because it applies only using the Javascript syntax settings with Codemirror and is not normally used in Joomla. 3rd party plugins might like to use it though. ', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-06 07:27:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(228, 228, NULL, 3, 'com_media: Auto-fill Image URL after upload', 'com_media is great, but uploading several images and having to find each one in the imagelist is a pain. This pull request addresses that issue by auto-filling the image url after successful upload via JApplication::setUserState() and JApplication::getUserState()<br><br>This solves tracker item - http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28624', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-06 12:29:05', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/228.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(229, 229, NULL, 3, 'Feature media #28176', 'See http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28176', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-06 15:17:23', '2012-06-10 05:32:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/229.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(230, 230, NULL, 3, 'Menu: Article Layout Selection', 'Found an issue in the Active Menu item where there was no way to choose a HTML override option for an article. If the article was a active menu and a layout override was chosen in the article it would not work. So a option was needed in the article menu to resolve this.<br><br>New option placed in the menu area for article selection called Choose Layout.<br>Updated logic to check for this new field in the view for com_content/view/article/<br><br>Signed-off-by: Steven <steven@corephp.com>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-06 18:00:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/230.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(231, 231, NULL, 3, 'Fixing language discover method', 'Already fixed in the platform but not in CMS. ', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-06 18:19:20', '2012-06-07 06:05:29', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/231.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(232, 232, NULL, 3, 'Fixes CodeMirror bug with JS syntax', '', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-07 01:13:25', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/232.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(233, 233, NULL, 3, '''continue'' used outside of loop context. Just return false instead.', 'Fix for this: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28630', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-08 07:07:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/233.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(234, 234, NULL, 3, 'Advanced ACL for com_modules, permissions per module', 'I noticed that a lot of people that are using the Joomla ACL system are looking for permission support per module and not just for the entire com_modules component. <br><br>This patch adds advanced ACL to com_modules and allows to set permissions (delete, edit & edit.state) per module. ', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-08 09:48:54', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/234.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(235, 235, NULL, 3, 'Modifying New User Account Activation Tooltip to be more specific about ...', '...intended behavior of Admin setting<br><br>See https://groups.google.com/d/topic/joomlabugsquad/3oHPSe248r0/discussion for more background information', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-08 17:02:47', '2012-06-09 05:10:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/235.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(236, 236, 28367, 3, ' [#28367] Cache does not cache header information', 'This pull request tries to fix the problem mentioned here:<br><br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28367<br><br>It adds the caching of header data (from JResponse::getHeaders()) and removes the use of ''Workarounds'' for the cache controller ''page'' because I don''t think that this is necessary for caching the complete output of a page (there were some problems with that, too).<br><br>If your tests are successful I will try to send this also to the Joomla! platform.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-09 14:15:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/236.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(237, 237, NULL, 3, 'Adding new hashing algorithms to Joomla 3.0', 'Tracker item: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8549&tracker_item_id=27381<br><br>Discussion: https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/joomla-dev-cms/mzb0utUj0wg<br><br>Made some slight changes, it uses bcrypt by default now. ', 3, 0, 10, '2012-06-10 21:26:21', '2012-06-10 21:36:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/237.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(238, 238, NULL, 3, 'Adding new hashing algorithms to Joomla 3.0', 'Tracker item: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8549&tracker_item_id=27381<br><br>Discussion link: https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/joomla-dev-cms/mzb0utUj0wg<br><br>Changes made: Made bcrypt the default algorithm when you install Joomla', 3, 0, 1, '2012-06-10 21:34:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/238.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
