(3216851, 45, 'infograf768', 'Language issues:\r<br>Back-end filters are double translated.\r<br>Take off true in\r<br><?php echo JHtml::_(''select.options'', JHtml::_(''finder.mapslist''), ''value'', ''text'', $this->state->get(''filter.branch''), true);?>\r<br>and\r<br><?php echo JHtml::_(''select.options'', JHtml::_(''finder.statelist''), ''value'', ''text'', $this->state->get(''filter.state''), true);?>\r<br>Remains Country an Region to deal with in Maps Manager. as 2 strings are missing:\r<br>COM_FINDER_TYPE_P_COUNTRY="Country"\r<br>COM_FINDER_TYPE_P_REGION="Region"\r<br>\r<br>Front-end\r<br>Same issue: take off true in\r<br>$html .= JHtml::_(''select.genericlist'', $nodes, ''t[]'', ''class="inputbox"'', ''id'', ''title'', $active, ''tax-'' . JFilterOutput::stringUrlSafe($bv->title), true);', '2011-12-20 10:05:38'),
(3217363, 45, 'infograf768', '// Activate the highlighter if enabled.\r<br>if (!empty($this->query->highlight) && $this->params->get(''highlight_terms'', 1)) {\r<br>	JHtml::_(''finder.highlighter'', $this->query->highlight);\r<br>}\r<br>\r<br>breaks search results here.\r<br>\r<br>IT looks also, here, that starting typing for joomla for example does not any more present a list of results dropping down from the search field', '2011-12-20 11:03:22'),
(3221060, 45, 'elinw', 'JM do you mean you are not getting suggested search terms? \r<br>\r<br>Chris, next time you might want to try a rebase, but all that happened is that the project cms has had tons of updates and you got them all. \r<br>\r<br>The highlighter issue should be fixed now.', '2011-12-20 16:22:02'),
