(5060719, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'Well, look, I managed to fight my way to the tracker submission page (twice) and submit the issue. But, of course, I was logged out as soon as I clicked the submit button and the issue did not appear in the list. \r<br>\r<br>Is there any person actually responsible for joomlacode who I could get some support from? Or was that site just set up years ago and left to rot? I see that issues have been posted to the tracker as recently as yesterday (or maybe it''s today, I''m probably a day ahead) so it seems to work for somebody. What is the secret? No, logging in twice doesn''t change a thing. \r<br>\r<br>Actually, I can go into more detail about the login problem. If I log in at http://joomlacode.org/gf/account/?action=Login I will get in and be redirected to ''My Page''. But almost any action gets me logged out and sent back to the login page with a ''redirect'' parameter. If I submit the login form while that parameter is in the url, I will always just end up back at the same login form. The only way I can successfully log in is to remove that parameter, but then I end up back at ''My Page'' and unable to get to other pages without being logged out again. I''m trying to be patient with this thing but it''s quite frustrating. ', '2012-04-11 02:00:25'),
(5068208, 179, 'doxadigital', 'i got this problem as well...\r<br>\r<br>i''m using windows, zend server, php 5.3.3 \r<br>\r<br>hope somebody able to solve it', '2012-04-11 13:05:58'),
(5068253, 179, 'atomtech', 'I get this same problem too!\r<br>\r<br>i''m using windows, zend server, php 5.3.9!', '2012-04-11 13:08:46'),
(5072938, 179, 'infograf768', 'At looking on the Net, it could be related to the use of Zend.', '2012-04-11 16:32:29'),
(5073844, 179, 'doxadigital', '@brunoferrari @mickles - do you guys use Zend Server as well ? ', '2012-04-11 17:14:53'),
(5084913, 188, 'infograf768', 'Please post a tracker on joomlacode and reference here.', '2012-04-12 05:49:14'),
(5084981, 179, 'infograf768', 'See:\r<br>https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688', '2012-04-12 05:58:15'),
(5085305, 179, 'mickles', '```infograf768 commented \r<br>See:\r<br> https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688\r<br>```\r<br>\r<br>so possibly the patch is:\r<br>```\r<br>I turned off warnings with ini_set before calling usort, then turned them on again after.  \r<br>This is an effective workaround for now, but I''d love to clean that nastiness out of my code.\r<br>```\r<br>\r<br>I''ll try it a little bit later...', '2012-04-12 06:41:40'),
(5085340, 179, 'mickles', 'And yes, I use windows\\zend \r<br>\r<br>```\r<br>PHP Built On\r<br>\r<br> Windows NT MICKLES7 6.1 build 7601 \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Database Version\r<br>\r<br> 5.5.12 \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Database Collation\r<br>\r<br> utf8_general_ci \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>PHP Version\r<br>\r<br> 5.2.17 \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Web Server\r<br>\r<br> Apache/2.2.16 (Win32) mod_ssl/2.2.16 OpenSSL/0.9.8o \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>WebServer to PHP Interface\r<br>\r<br> cgi-fcgi \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Joomla! Version\r<br>\r<br> Joomla! 2.5.3 Stable [ Ember ] 15-March-2012 14:00 GMT \r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>Joomla! Platform Version\r<br>\r<br> Joomla Platform 11.4.0 Stable [ Brian Kernighan ] 03-Jan-2012 00:00 GMT \r<br>\r<br>```\r<br>\r<br>', '2012-04-12 06:45:46'),
(5085431, 179, 'doxadigital', 'i wonder if the bug is within the php itself, people should ''scream'' at the moment, but in fact it happen to most zend server user.... ', '2012-04-12 06:54:03'),
(5086946, 188, 'sybrek', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28398', '2012-04-12 08:49:03'),
(5091928, 181, 'elinw', 'Yes it works really well for dozens of people everyday.  I''ve asked Sam to take a look at if there is a problem with your account. ', '2012-04-12 14:17:43'),
(5106189, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'elinw, thanks, I hope it can be fixed soon. \r<br>\r<br>realityking, thanks for the feedback. I think I should first modify the upload function so that it works whether Filedata is an array or not (well, it''s always an array but you know what I mean). After that, it will up to the template to either use this feature or stick with single file uploads. As to the doctype, do you know if there is any plan to switch to HTML5 or any reason not to do so? ', '2012-04-13 00:30:09'),
(5106409, 181, 'realityking', 'I''m pretty sure we''re gonna switch to the HTML5 Doctype for 3.0, not sure we wanna touch that for 2.5.\r<br>\r<br>Personally I don''t mind the invalid attribute too much, also I''d be willing to trade the small change required to layout overrides for simpler code but at the end that''s a call to be made by leadership.', '2012-04-13 00:49:38'),
(5106418, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'Oh, and I''ve added a couple of functions but I didn''t add a ''@since''. What will be the next version?', '2012-04-13 00:50:05'),
(5106544, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'As you can see, getting it to work properly whether or not multiple is set in the template doesn''t really complicate the code in any significant way. Probably better to be a little more robust and backward compatible here. That being said, the built in templates don''t seem to override this page. Maybe some 3rd party ones do? Are there 3rd party admin templates? ', '2012-04-13 01:00:46'),
(5109189, 189, 'infograf768', 'Please add a tracker on joomlacode and put reference here', '2012-04-13 06:36:38'),
(5110031, 190, 'infograf768', 'Please cretae a tracker on Joomlacode and add reference here.', '2012-04-13 07:52:17'),
(5110065, 190, 'fititnt', 'This http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28403 ?', '2012-04-13 07:55:33'),
(5112953, 189, 'rvsjoen', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28404', '2012-04-13 11:42:21'),
(5113256, 190, 'garyamort', 'Note: the point of it not being of type submit in that instance is because it is not allowed to have no search terms specified.  It prevents the user from submitting the form if they don''t enter anything.  There is an onclick javascript which modified it from to a submit button when data has been entered.   As such, for a small change it is better to make it of type button rather then submit.  Mind you, I think it''s better to validate server side and always let it be a submit button - use the javascript onClick event to validate, but for those who have javascript disabled let them submit and catch it server side.  But that''s a more involved bit of code.', '2012-04-13 12:04:49'),
(5115081, 191, 'infograf768', 'Please make a tracker on joomlacode and add reference here.', '2012-04-13 14:01:25'),
(5116606, 191, 'mbabker', 'This code should actually be removed.  The `$_observers` array in JDispatcher is protected and unable to be accessed from the indexer helper.\r<br>\r<br>The best practice is for plugins to check for the `com_finder.indexer` context.  Otherwise, there really isn''t anything that can be done within the indexer''s code.', '2012-04-13 15:12:32'),
(5122615, 191, 'garyamort', '"Please make a tracker on joomlacode and add reference here." - no. :-)\r<br>\r<br>Sorry, I lack the time to learn how to navigate yet another system.  I''ll offer the change for those who decide they want it.  Beyond that though I lack time.', '2012-04-13 18:48:11'),
(5122841, 191, 'garyamort', ''' The $_observers array in JDispatcher is protected and unable to be accessed from the indexer helper.''... hmm, it worked for me.  I must have subclassed the JDispatcher class in order to get around that..  ugly hack...  I guess I could go back and swap it out calls to detach instead...  I''ll put that on my todo list.....  low, but there. :-)', '2012-04-13 18:59:18'),
(5145850, 190, 'fititnt', 'I realized that beyond the problem of validation, Joomla 2.5.4, when accessed via IE7 (at least via IE9 with browser mode IE7), com_finder component button does not work. Test can be done on http://demo17.cloudaccess.net/using-joomla/extensions/components/search-component/smart-search.html . With enter on text field still working. This happens because IE7 need that button element has an explicit value  equals to "submit" on type. So at least commit:137d207, the fist of this thread, solve this.\r<br>\r<br>On commit:e7d5cd7 already has javascript to enable and disable submit via button and via pressing enter on input search field on component, and make possible change minimum length via template override, but still not make any additional check on back end, but I can do it.\r<br>\r<br>Anyway. is allowed (or not a bad idea) to change "Allow Empty Search" or even add a new option on backend of com_finder for 2.5, or must wait for 3.0? Could be interesting to make possible flexible minimum length, because just one letter still more than one empty value, and at least two letters appears more reasonable.', '2012-04-16 05:06:36'),
(5146083, 190, 'mbabker', 'Seems like sound logic to me.  I''ll test later on my Windows system to see how things behave.', '2012-04-16 05:39:09'),
(5149338, 185, 'infograf768', 'Please let it know in the tracker when ready to test.', '2012-04-16 10:11:31'),
(5163769, 181, 'realityking', 'There are a few other admin templates, for example [AdminPraise](http://adminpraise.com/).', '2012-04-16 22:05:35'),
(5165489, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'I see. Well, in any case, this change should not break the functionality of any template.', '2012-04-17 00:04:14'),
(5175983, 192, 'infograf768', 'This issue has already been committed to Platform and is RTC in jjomlacode.\r<br>See: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28364', '2012-04-17 14:15:41'),
(5194580, 159, 'infograf768', 'Committed via eclipse.', '2012-04-18 09:09:14'),
(5208570, 154, 'ercanozkaya', 'Those who need to work this around can use something like this: \r<br>JFactory::getSession()->set(''com_docman.fix.the.session.bug'', microtime(true));', '2012-04-18 20:55:42'),
(5209256, 154, 'oc666', '@ercanozkaya don''t forget to update you session table to be able to contain all the microtime:\r<br>ALTER TABLE #__#__session MODIFY COLUMN time varchar(15) DEFAULT '''';', '2012-04-18 21:29:20'),
(5209318, 154, 'ercanozkaya', '@oc666 Not needed for the workaround. This just changes something in the session data so that the database query will return an affected row.', '2012-04-18 21:32:32'),
(5221635, 193, 'dgasparri', 'getInstance() should also be cleaned and simplified, as it does stuff proper of a factory pattern and factory method (choosing which class to load). Not knowing if there was backward compatibility issues, I left it like that.\r<br>\r<br>Part of the "reasoning" in getInstance() about the environment variables ($_REQUEST task, controller, option, and so on) are left intact in the getInstance(), but were duplicated cleared and streamlined into the createEnvironmentArray() method.', '2012-04-19 13:36:22'),
(5235930, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'Slight change of subject so maybe I should start a new thread but [this](http://filepicker.io/) looks pretty good. I might try to write a module for it if I have some spare time. Any thoughts?', '2012-04-20 00:52:09'),
(5244993, 195, 'Balleno', 'query in business.php:\r<br>\r<br>$db->setQuery("SELECT #__bd_packages.picture_num FROM #__bd_businesses\r<br>LEFT JOIN #__bd_packages ON #__bd_packages.id=#__bd_businesses.package_id WHERE\r<br>#__bd_businesses.id=".JRequest::getVar(''id''));', '2012-04-20 14:21:45'),
(5266934, 194, 'dgasparri', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28441', '2012-04-22 10:39:06'),
(5266939, 193, 'dgasparri', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28441', '2012-04-22 10:39:35'),
(5282120, 196, 'florianv', '2 ° commit) I think the $strict param complicates things for nothing, and is never used in any "core extension" call.\r<br>Moreover, I don''t get why the OR is there, because it''s independent from the frontend/backend.', '2012-04-23 14:21:58'),
