(5656258, 205, 'mbabker', 'PHP in most instances is able to handle paths with either type of and both slashes in it.', '2012-05-11 17:24:22'),
(5668633, 124, 'gpongelli', 'Good pull request, hope will be merged soon.<br>Let me know, so I can update my PostgreSQL pull.<br><br>Eng. Gabriele Pongelli', '2012-05-12 13:54:28'),
(5682710, 168, 'aaronschmitz', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28525', '2012-05-14 05:00:51'),
(5743295, 153, 'azrul', 'The problem is real and does need fixing, but the commit is actually bad, and I am pretty strongly against merging this into the core.', '2012-05-16 15:10:42'),
(5753793, 210, 'elinw', 'You don''t want to totally remove permissions from the component since those provide the fall backs that are used in absence of specific settings.  Ideally you only use the item level ones in special cases, similar to the article level permissions in content.', '2012-05-16 22:25:48'),
(5758856, 210, 'infograf768', 'Also, please add a Feature Tracker on joomlacode an reference back here:<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&tracker_id=8549<br><br>Forgot:<br>You are deleting in this patch a new string just committed:<br>COM_MENUS_ITEM_FIELD_HIDE_UNASSIGNED="Hide Unassigned Modules"', '2012-05-17 06:04:42'),
(5759814, 153, 'piotr-cz', 'There is another commit for the issule: https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/1209', '2012-05-17 07:51:12'),
(5762624, 153, 'elinw', 'Jonah and Azrul could you comment on #1209 as an alternative solution? ', '2012-05-17 11:57:47'),
(5764724, 210, 'rmcdaniel', 'I didn''t remove the component permissions. I just moved them to the access.xml file along with the menu type and menu item permissions. Also, I see now in this patch that I didn''t use the newest files when I made my changes. I''ll close this request, fix it, create a feature tracker and then submit a new pull request. Thanks!', '2012-05-17 14:11:09'),
(5768715, 210, 'elinw', 'You shouldn''t need to move the access.xml from where it was.', '2012-05-17 17:08:10'),
(5770051, 210, 'rmcdaniel', 'When I started, com_menus didn''t have an access.xml. I created it and then moved the component permissions to the new access.xml from config.xml so it would look more like com_content. Looking at the commit, I don''t think the access.xml I created got added. Sorry for the confusion, I''m a bit new to Git.', '2012-05-17 18:04:14'),
(5801359, 210, 'elinw', 'Oh I see it was just using the default.', '2012-05-19 12:27:34'),
(5821509, 179, 'doxadigital', 'already a month away.. hope somebody have the solution..', '2012-05-21 12:46:54'),
(5827061, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28552', '2012-05-21 16:30:38'),
(5827713, 212, 'realityking', 'Haven''t tested it yet but the idea is awesome!<br><br>Note: We''ll have to update the sample data after this has landed.', '2012-05-21 16:56:26'),
(5832394, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'I forgot something else. In order to install properly, in installation/sql/mysql/joomla.sql this line:<br><br>INSERT INTO `#__menu_types` VALUES (1, ''mainmenu'', ''Main Menu'', ''The main menu for the site'');<br><br>should be:<br><br>INSERT INTO `#__menu_types` VALUES (1, 0, ''mainmenu'', ''Main Menu'', ''The main menu for the site'');<br><br>How do I add this to the pull request? Or should I make a new one?', '2012-05-21 20:09:08'),
(5832516, 212, 'realityking', 'You can just add another commit to your branch, it will automatically be part of the pull request.<br><br>Another note that just occured to me: We probably need a migration script for this. I''m pretty sure something weird will happen if there isn''t an entry in the asset table for a menu or menu item.', '2012-05-21 20:13:48'),
(5832685, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'Thanks for the help.<br><br>Regarding the migration script, when I was working on this, I started by just doing ALTER TABLE to add the asset_id column. Everything defaulted to 0 asset_id and nothing blew up. That might be enough.', '2012-05-21 20:21:56'),
(5841433, 212, 'infograf768', 'Created an update sql file containing<br>ALTER TABLE  `#__menu_types` ADD COLUMN `asset_id` INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT ''0'' COMMENT ''FK to the #__assets table.'' AFTER `id`;<br>ALTER TABLE  `#__menu` ADD COLUMN `asset_id` INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT ''0'' COMMENT ''FK to the #__assets table.'' AFTER `id`;<br><br>Ran it and then tested on existing site<br><br>saw some errors preventing the tmpl from displaying wen editing a menu item<br><br>$canDo		= $this->canDo;  // error<br>$canDoAlso	= $this->canDoAlso;  //error<br><br>Also some errors with divs in views/item/tmpl/edit.php', '2012-05-22 07:57:18'),
(5850636, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'Alright, this latest commit should fix the problems that infograf768 saw.', '2012-05-22 15:49:10'),
(5866055, 212, 'infograf768', 'The above errors are now corrected.<br>@test<br>Default Administrator has no access to menus/menu items permissions.', '2012-05-23 06:28:14'),
(5879553, 213, 'infograf768', 'Tracker is: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28561<br>needs one more tester', '2012-05-23 17:33:57'),
(5882408, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'I fixed the permissions for new installations. For current installations you need to execute:<br><br>UPDATE #__assets SET rules = ''{"core.admin":{"7":1},"core.manage":{"6":1},"core.create":{"3":1},"core.delete":[],"core.edit":{"4":1},"core.edit.state":{"5":1},"core.edit.own":[]}'' WHERE id = 16;', '2012-05-23 19:34:39'),
(5892088, 212, 'infograf768', '@ test<br>This does not work here.', '2012-05-24 05:24:17'),
(5892272, 214, 'infograf768', 'Please add a tracker in the Joomla Feature Tracker on joomlacode ( http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&tracker_id=8549 )<br>Also, this pull is so incomplete that it cannot be tested. ', '2012-05-24 05:30:15'),
(5893143, 214, 'Twentronix', 'I''ve added some changes and options. It''s working fine and in my opinion it''s ready for a pull right now. Also added a tracker: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28565. Please advice.', '2012-05-24 05:48:55'),
(5894373, 214, 'Twentronix', 'Test instructions (J!2.5)<br><br>1- Overwrite your J2.5 files:<br>https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/214/files<br>2- Go to article manager in back-end Joomla. <br>3- Options -> Integration -> JGLOBAL_FEED_SHOW_READMORE_LABEL: Show<br>4- Add some articles, split them with readmore. Create menu-item of type<br>category. Maybe you need to use the syndication module to get the RSS feed<br>link.<br>5- Go to your RSS feed for that category with Firefox:<br>view-source:http://your-rss-feed.com<br>6- Now you can see the read more links in the descriptions. You can turn them<br>off with step 3.', '2012-05-24 07:27:41'),
(5895363, 214, 'infograf768', 'Corrected your patch. See joomlacode tracker. As I commented there, I see no use for the Read More.', '2012-05-24 08:41:34'),
(5915048, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'The only thing I can think of is that maybe the group and/or asset ids are different on your dataset.', '2012-05-24 19:15:11'),
(5924437, 212, 'infograf768', 'I am using default trunk install with sampledata, patched with your diff and both queries.<br>I suggest you test this environment', '2012-05-25 06:54:07'),
(5924801, 198, 'piotr-cz', 'cool, thanks!', '2012-05-25 07:28:06'),
(5924852, 205, 'piotr-cz', '@pietjepel What value did you put into $live_site param?', '2012-05-25 07:32:28'),
(5971089, 174, 'marcusds', 'Why is this still not fixed? Major pain.', '2012-05-28 19:53:52'),
(5974668, 174, 'mbabker', 'This should be fixed in the current code as it appears to have been committed after 2.5.4''s release.  So, it should be included in 2.5.5.  If you are testing the current development code and it isn''t fixed, please submit a new issue.', '2012-05-29 02:13:53'),
(5994006, 195, 'Balleno', 'I have found the source of the problem.<br>It was in a custom list field with the following line:<br>$query = new JDatabaseQuery;<br>The "new JDatabaseQuery" is probably not supported any more in 2.5,<br>so it only works with the following:<br>$query = $db->getQuery(true); - where $db id the database object.', '2012-05-29 19:56:58'),
(6026837, 218, 'jlleblanc', 'Also, a jQuery integration plan has been added here: http://docs.joomla.org/JavaScript_Working_Group#jQuery_Integration_Plan', '2012-05-31 02:58:19'),
(6028508, 216, 'infograf768', 'Please create a new tracker on joomlacode. Add testing instructions. Cross-reference here. ', '2012-05-31 05:49:40'),
(6028511, 217, 'infograf768', 'Please create a new tracker on joomlacode. Add testing instructions. Cross-reference here. ', '2012-05-31 05:50:02'),
(6028555, 218, 'infograf768', 'Please create a Joomla Feature tracker in http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&tracker_id=8549 and reference here.', '2012-05-31 05:54:31'),
(6034251, 218, 'laoneo', 'Can''t wait till jQuery will be available in joomla core!! The folk of the G4J project will thank you...I think jQuery.noConflict(); should be in a separate file. Users which care abut site speed do have a javascript minifier like jFinalizer installed anyway which packs all javascript files into one....', '2012-05-31 12:15:37'),
(6034338, 219, 'infograf768', 'Please create a tracker on joomlacode and cross reference here.', '2012-05-31 12:20:22'),
(6034419, 217, 'krileon', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8103&tracker_item_id=28591', '2012-05-31 12:25:22'),
(6034431, 216, 'krileon', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8103&tracker_item_id=28591', '2012-05-31 12:25:44'),
(6035132, 219, 'laoneo', 'Here it is http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8103&tracker_item_id=28592', '2012-05-31 13:03:14'),
(6036398, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '@rmcdaniel great idea to add ACL support to menu''s! Much requested feature among the users of Joomla ACL.<br><br>Just started testing this new feature, and during the installation of fresh site with sampledata errors are visible while installing sampledata. The reason for this is that for example "installation/sql/mysql/sample_data.sq" should be updates as well with asset_id values for the #__menu and #__menu_types. Same for any other sample data file. In addition to this there should be references for all menu items and menus in the #__assets table as well.', '2012-05-31 13:54:52'),
(6036829, 212, 'infograf768', '@sanderpotjer<br>Indeed. This is what I tried to convey above. If we want to implemnt this for 3.x, we will not only have to change sampledatas, but also provide a migration for existing sites.', '2012-05-31 14:12:25'),
(6036987, 218, 'jlleblanc', 'Feature Tracker item created: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28593', '2012-05-31 14:17:57'),
(6036995, 218, 'gnomeontherun', 'I recommend adding jQuery.noConflict(); to the end of the jQuery file.', '2012-05-31 14:18:17'),
(6037373, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'Thanks for the information. I''ll try to get the sample data and the assets done today. As for the migration script, can you give me any ideas on how to start? Is there an example in the installation folder already? Any documentation? Another thing that someone with more experience could look at is how I implemented _getAssetParentId(). I think it might be supposed to return the menutype id, or maybe it should return the parent menu item if that exists?', '2012-05-31 14:31:10'),
(6037583, 212, 'infograf768', 'We do not have any migration script in present trunk. Just some simple updates to the db in com_admin.', '2012-05-31 14:39:26'),
(6037980, 218, 'kyleledbetter', 'Not sure if this question or request belongs here, but should we also offer a toggle to use a CDN/hosted version of jQuery in the core? Thx for working on this btw', '2012-05-31 14:54:47'),
(6042956, 212, 'sanderpotjer', 'Actually, the core.edit.own action is not needed in this component at the moment. There is no information stored in the menu tables about the creators of menutypes/menus. So it is better to remove the entire core.edit.own action for this component or we need to extend the menu tables with the creator information. ', '2012-05-31 18:00:28'),
(6043236, 212, 'rmcdaniel', 'Does that mean I should remove it from the menu section as well?', '2012-05-31 18:11:32'),
(6043328, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '@rmcdaniel yes that is correct to remove core.edit.own from the menu section as well. Sorry for the confusing btw, just noticed edit.own isn''t possible at the moment, so better to remove it for now.', '2012-05-31 18:15:18'),
(6043603, 212, 'sanderpotjer', 'Another thing I noticed, when installing new components an entry in the #__menu table is created for each of the backend menu items of the component (this is currently default in Joomla). Now with this new menu ACL an entry in the assets table is created as well, but missing the correct parent and level id''s. This is more difficult to fix because there is no ''menutype'' for the backend menu items. <br><br>This might be solved if the backend menu will be transformed in a similar system as the frontend menus. I know there are plans for that, but don''t know the status of that. So need to look into this (but want to share it already).', '2012-05-31 18:25:31'),
(6045768, 218, 'jlleblanc', '@kyleledbetter yup, that''s part of what I''m asking. I know we''re loathe to add more options in the configuration.php file and a plugin seems overweight. I''m wondering if we might want to introduce an "extended" configuration panel for Joomla 3.0 that isn''t tied to configuration.php and would allow for later-breaking features like this.<br><br>@gnomeontherun I lean towards appending `jQuery.noConflict();` directly to the file as well. Some people brought up the fact that this adds One More Thing To Remember To Do whenever a new version of jQuery comes out, which is a valid concern.', '2012-05-31 19:54:23'),
(6045835, 218, 'gnomeontherun', '@jlleblanc valid concern, but also something that could be automated during the build process.', '2012-05-31 19:57:24'),
(6046673, 218, 'beat', 'Hi all,<br>For reference here is my pull request which might be reviewed with "new eyes" now that jQuery inclusion has been decided:<br>https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/736<br><br>For pre- and post- javascript files inclusions javascript code (required for CDN downloading of jquery) you can take a look at the proposed patches for the 2 files:<br>libraries/joomla/document/document.php<br>libraries/joomla/document/html/renderer/head.php<br><br>here:<br><br>https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/736/files<br><br>Pretty easy to do and would do that job and solve many other valid uses of defining JS variables before including JS files...<br><br>I''m still to avoid changing imported libraries, and above solution is clean, elegant and same inclusion if from joomla install (which should be default for security reasons) or from a CDN.<br><br>Finally, changes to file:<br>libraries/joomla/html/html/behavior.php<br>on that page allow to solve all the dependencies of jQuery plugins, and at same time of jquery versioning.<br><br>Let me know what you think, and if there are parts that you think are not useful.', '2012-05-31 20:33:20'),
(6049680, 220, 'sanderpotjer', 'JoomlaCode: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28595', '2012-05-31 22:53:19'),
(6051229, 218, 'jlleblanc', '@beat ah, yes, I''d forgotten that the CDN was one of the reasons appending noConflict to the end was a non-starter.', '2012-06-01 00:41:34'),
(6059532, 166, 'JoaoSRaposo', 'Hello gpongelli,<br><br>Really nice work. <br>Postgres support is very important to easily integrate Joomla with other applications that are using postgres DB.<br><br>Thank you very much for you work and hope this pull request will be included in next Joomla release.', '2012-06-01 12:43:53'),
(6060083, 124, 'realityking', 'I think this has already been committed. Please confirm & close. Thanks.', '2012-06-01 13:16:02'),
(6060093, 218, 'DaveOzric', 'This would be simply awesome!', '2012-06-01 13:16:28'),
(6060219, 124, 'mbabker', 'It''s been committed.', '2012-06-01 13:23:30'),
(6068090, 153, 'realityking', 'Shouldn''t we rather try to make sure that every key is unique? Or is there a reason why we can''t guarantee that?', '2012-06-01 18:55:08'),
(6068093, 153, 'realityking', 'Shouldn''t we rather try to make sure that every key is unique? Or is there a reason why we can''t guarantee that?', '2012-06-01 18:55:10'),
(6068186, 208, 'realityking', 'Could you open an issue on the tracker for this? Thanks.', '2012-06-01 18:58:47'),
(6068567, 208, 'amh-mw', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28604', '2012-06-01 19:16:16'),
(6072882, 153, 'elinw', 'That''s the approach of #1209', '2012-06-01 23:20:35'),
(6072987, 212, 'elinw', 'In what sense is there ownership in menus?<br>the edit.own  management is very messy to start out with since it violates a number of principles of ACL. There were very good reasons it was decided not to implement it below the category level for anything but articles in 1.6+.  <br><br>You need to look at com_categories as that is the only core component that has a table extending jtablenested. That should show you how to work with nesting correctly.', '2012-06-01 23:29:44'),
(6073591, 208, 'elinw', 'Wouldn''t it be better to move these to the cms folder than to have a cms specific modification in the joomla folder?', '2012-06-02 00:30:43'),
(6075274, 213, 'elinw', 'I think this should be 2.5 not 1.6. It''s changing history to call it 1.6.<br><br><br><br>', '2012-06-02 06:18:50'),
(6075740, 213, 'realityking', 'All of these classes and methods were also present in 1.6.0 so I felt this to be more accurate.', '2012-06-02 08:07:20'),
(6075798, 208, 'realityking', 'The fix isn''t so much CMS specific than already fixed in the platform. Just in a different way we probably don''t wanna do for 2.5.x (these classes are now autoloadable in the platform)', '2012-06-02 08:17:49'),
(6076708, 221, 'sanderpotjer', 'JoomlaCode: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28610', '2012-06-02 11:16:07'),
(6079126, 144, 'gnomeontherun', 'Just FYI, my proposed work with the admin menu will end up removing this. It uses the same concepts as the frontend menu for the most part.', '2012-06-02 17:11:25'),
(6079427, 190, 'elinw', 'The reason you allow for no terms is because you mght be using the filters and no terms at all.<br><br>Is this good to go? have people tested it? If so will you please report on the tracker so we can make it rtc or if not can we make it not pending anymore?', '2012-06-02 17:51:09'),
(6079786, 208, 'elinw', 'That''s what I''m saying I think. Rather than modify the CMS version of the platform why don''t we add to  cms? I think we should try to keep thing as clean as possible.', '2012-06-02 18:45:34'),
(6080765, 208, 'realityking', 'Define clean? If you mean 11.4 - well than I should probably not backport all that stuff from the platform ;)<br><br>Seriously there''s no harm in adding this. Yes it will be overwritten by the next full platform sync, but that''s fine because it''s a better - and fully compatible - fix.', '2012-06-02 21:13:09'),
(6100238, 208, 'amh-mw', 'If it helps clarify this patch,<br><br>libraries/joomla/access/access.php<br>13	+jimport(''joomla.application.component.helper'');<br><br>fixes the JComponentHelper dependencies found in the same file at<br><br>288	$result = array(JComponentHelper::getParams(''com_users'')->get(''guest_usergroup'',<br>1));<br>301	$query->where(''a.id = '' . (int)<br>JComponentHelper::getParams(''com_users'')->get(''guest_usergroup'', 1));<br><br>and<br><br>libraries/joomla/installer/installer.php<br>17	+jimport(''joomla.event.dispatcher'');<br><br>fixes the JDispatcher dependencies found in the same file at<br><br>466	$dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>544	$dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>658	$dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>710	$dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();', '2012-06-04 14:31:25'),
(6116477, 218, 'jlleblanc', 'I''ve now added updates for "post scripts" to be added immediately after linked scripts. I''ve also added the possibility of using a CDN URL in place of a local copy of jQuery.', '2012-06-05 02:43:36'),
(6117915, 190, 'fititnt', '@elinw for me still ok from my last commit on this pull. But before do a merge, need confirmation that more people tested it just to be sure.<br><br>Also, if someone think that have a better way to do it, I can work a bit more on this pull. I will just avoid big changes before 3.0. I have a few ideas but they change com_finder parameters on administrator and could break layouts, so are not a good idea for Joomla 2.5 LTS and still better at least do in a different pull.', '2012-06-05 05:37:25'),
(6144463, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '@elinw <br><br>I seem to have worked this out. It looks like it was something to do with my company''s network after all. I don''t understand it but at least I have a solution.<br><br>Now, to post a report (and I have several) I need to associate it with a ''project''? There are heaps of projects on joomlacode, most of them look like 3rd party plugins. Is there a project just for com_media or would this be considered as part of some core Joomla project? I also have things to post about CodeMirror, what project would that be listed as?', '2012-06-06 07:18:09'),
(6149916, 181, 'mbabker', 'This will link you right to the CMS Bug Tracker: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&tracker_id=8103', '2012-06-06 13:01:19'),
