(6175872, 223, 'infograf768', 'Fixed through Eclipse.', '2012-06-07 13:35:36'),
(6180259, 181, 'elinw', 'No don''t do a project, you want this to be part of the core Joomla cms<br>project.<br><br>Elin<br><br>On Wed, Jun 6, 2012 at 3:18 AM, Elijah Madden <<br>reply@reply.github.com<br>> wrote:<br><br>> @elinw<br>><br>> I seem to have worked this out. It looks like it was something to do with<br>> my company''s network after all. I don''t understand it but at least I have a<br>> solution.<br>><br>> Now, to post a report (and I have several) I need to associate it with a<br>> ''project''? There are heaps of projects on joomlacode, most of them look<br>> like 3rd party plugins. Is there a project just for com_media or would this<br>> be considered as part of some core Joomla project? I also have things to<br>> post about CodeMirror, what project would that be listed as?<br>><br>> ---<br>> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:<br>> https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/181#issuecomment-6144463<br>>', '2012-06-07 16:14:16'),
(6196898, 168, 'infograf768', 'Fixed with eclipse. Thanks.', '2012-06-08 08:25:40'),
