(7676741, 306, 'elinw', 'Replaces #301<br><br>https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/1431 deals with some notices that show if you have error reporting on and put in a bad url.<br><br>Feature tracker:<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=28905', '2012-08-12 15:30:51'),
(7677131, 306, 'realityking', 'JFeed will need some love to get this ready, just from a casual look I saw it''s using JXMLElement everywhere which is deprecated. The alternative is SimpleXMLElement. Also we have to change the docblocks to make this a CMS library.', '2012-08-12 16:13:08'),
(7679115, 306, 'elinw', 'JFeed is actually working fine, I''ve done a lot of testing and it does the\r<br>simple tasks required of it in com_newsfeed and mod_feed  as well as\r<br>simplepie.  You''re right about the docblocks though, forget to do them this\r<br>round. Will send an update in a few hours.\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>On Sun, Aug 12, 2012 at 12:13 PM, Rouven Weßling\r<br><notifications@github.com>wrote:\r<br>\r<br>> JFeed will need some love to get this ready, just from a casual look I saw\r<br>> it''s using JXMLElement everywhere which is deprecated. The alternative is\r<br>> SimpleXMLElement. Also we have to change the docblocks to make this a CMS\r<br>> library.\r<br>>\r<br>> —\r<br>> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub<https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/306#issuecomment-7677131>.\r<br>>\r<br>>', '2012-08-12 19:41:11'),
(7679375, 306, 'mbabker', 'It''s not that the code doesn''t work, we''re just trying to not introduce any deprecated code usage into the CMS.  Switching from JXMLElement to SimpleXMLElement is as simple as a find/replace action.', '2012-08-12 20:15:50'),
(7682924, 306, 'elinw', '@realityking It would be very helpful to have the needed fix to JHttpTransportSocket that has been sitting in the platform tracker for a while merged. <br><br>Ok updated and should be working', '2012-08-13 03:36:56'),
(7711445, 306, 'elinw', 'oops I thought  I pushed that 12 hours ago', '2012-08-13 23:13:24'),
(7761299, 307, 'realityking', 'Ah good this resurfaces :)<br><br>3 points:<br>1. This doesn''t merge right now<br>2. I don''t think we need all these SQL for changes to the databases since no one will update form a Joomla 2.5 postgres installation.<br>3. Please submit the changes to files in libraries/joomla to the platform so they can be merged over there first.', '2012-08-15 16:41:52'),
(7761527, 307, 'gpongelli', 'Hi Rouven,\r<br>1. Why isn''t it mergeable ?\r<br>2. You''re right, these files coming from old pull request and I''ve leaved them because I''ve found same files under mysql folder.\r<br>3. There''s an open pull request for platform project about these changes at least two months old.\r<br>\r<br>Gabriele Pongelli', '2012-08-15 16:50:28'),
(7761732, 307, 'realityking', 'Hey Gabriele,<br><br>I don''t know what the problem is, github just tells me it can''t automatically be merged. Ideally you just update it to current master, since there hasn''t been many commits the past two days it shouldn''t be a big problem.<br><br>You probably mean this platform pull https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/307, don''t you?<br><br>This doesn''t contain the changes to JSessionStorageDatabase and JTable. Could you submit them separately?<br>', '2012-08-15 16:57:39'),
(7762375, 307, 'mbabker', 'The commit to make FinderIndexer abstract is the likely cause of the merge issue.<br><br>Gabrielle, I abstracted out FinderIndexer so that child classes could be built for each database driver to run the indexer in a way that is optimized for that environment.  So, could you add a FinderIndexerDriverPostgresql class (you should be able to use the MySQL class as a base) and then you can modify the queries in that class to make them work best in Postgres (I have a patch doing the same for SQL Server).', '2012-08-15 17:18:54'),
