(8299558, 317, 'pjwiseman', 'I''m struggling with commit 127c374, the "merge remote tracking branch remotes/upstream/master".  I''m hoping someone better versed in joomla''s use of git can give that the ok or not ok.  When I merge to my own fresh master I get a merge tree that doesn''t clearly distinguish the changes in this pull.  The merge is valid - it''s simply how it is presented.  When refreshing to the current master, I generally do a rebase, create a new pull request, and close the old one, which is a pain.  I don''t know whether there is a cleaner way - we''re all new to git.<br><br>UPDATE: The word is that the upstream merge is ok.  This history isn''t necessarily as clean, but it works.', '2012-09-05 13:56:27'),
