(9214240, 332, 'pjwiseman', 'Closing.  For reference, the 2.5 fix is at https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/334\r<br>', '2012-10-08 00:37:41'),
(9217899, 482, 'infograf768', 'Fixed with Eclipse.', '2012-10-08 07:13:08'),
(9244836, 472, 'phproberto', 'Tracker issue:\r<br>\r<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=29428', '2012-10-09 00:04:53'),
(9267345, 465, 'mahagr', 'I''m really not sure why there needs to be a hit counter for the category. I cannot find a reason why I would like to know how many times one particular category has been visited.', '2012-10-09 16:01:44'),
(9267581, 479, 'mahagr', 'There are a few like this, but they all come from deprecated code. I would ignore fixing this "issue" as it helps extension developers to get rid of the old code.', '2012-10-09 16:08:02'),
(9267867, 472, 'mahagr', 'With this fix: what happens if you rename the article alias from the backend?\r<br>\r<br>Q: Should the old links keep up working?', '2012-10-09 16:14:22'),
(9269881, 472, 'juliopontes', '@mahagr No, they get recent alias field in db. So if you change You should get a error/404 page.', '2012-10-09 17:09:52'),
(9270591, 472, 'mahagr', 'In my humble opinion breaking all the links from Google isn''t that good idea administrator decides to change the alias -- at least not if the behaviour was different before and there''s a way to find out article ID.\r<br>\r<br>There''s also another major drawback on this fix -- I''ve seen many URLs from coming from both older versions of Joomla and other extensions that do not add alias to the article name. So your change is likely to break a few links which were working before.\r<br>\r<br>Better way to deal with the issue would force redirect if the URL of the article isn''t correct (e.g. was renamed or the generated link was missing alias).', '2012-10-09 17:30:06'),
(9273213, 472, 'phproberto', '@mahagr I think that you misunderstood what this patch does. It doesn''t break anything, just fixes the expected behaviour of the content URLs.\r<br>\r<br>If you change the alias of an article is because you want to change the URL. You can keep the old alias or if you want to change the alias and keep the old URL working you should create a redirection from the old url to the new URL. \r<br>\r<br>Extensions should use JRoute to generate valid URLs. Don''t fix a bug because some extensions are badly programmed has no sense to me.', '2012-10-09 18:24:55'),
(9273743, 472, 'phproberto', 'We are almost there Júlio.\r<br>\r<br>I have added two files Joomla! standards validation as example of remaining issues. Available if needed to help you to setup CodeSniffer working.', '2012-10-09 18:39:21'),
(9275854, 465, 'phproberto', ' I probably will not use it also but it isn''t so strange that someone does it. If the field is there why not use it?\r<br>\r<br>But I''m going to ensure that the hit counter is shown inthe backend as it does in the article management!\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>', '2012-10-09 19:33:33'),
(9285464, 472, 'juliopontes', '@phproberto  please check. ', '2012-10-10 00:43:02'),
(9287736, 490, 'mbabker', 'Hathor''s submenu has never been designed to be loaded within the component area, which was the reason we had to keep mod_submenu working.  Yes, the submenu is restored, but if it is going to be below the toolbar as you''ve placed it, within the component area, the styling needs to change.  The tab styling does not work here anymore.', '2012-10-10 01:58:11'),
(9288237, 490, 'shumisha', 'Hi Michael. You could not "keep the module working". It suffered the same issue that caused its removal from the main cms branch. I actually never saw Hathor design with sub menu, so I first simply restoredbthe full functinality, and it looked ''ok'' to me. Can you elaborate on what''s not working with tabs?', '2012-10-10 02:32:10'),
(9288289, 490, 'mbabker', 'It works, but the styling is way off.\r<br>\r<br>With this patch - http://awesomescreenshot.com/0a6inqq9d\r<br>\r<br>From 2.5 - http://awesomescreenshot.com/01ainqu27\r<br>\r<br>To assume the position that you''re proposing, the styling should change IMO.  It just doesn''t look right in that spot.\r<br>\r<br>Sorry if I''ve come across a little harsh at times.  Working hard, not a lot of sleep, and been easily irritable as of late.', '2012-10-10 02:37:14'),
(9288374, 490, 'shumisha', 'I know that, close to 5am here. Styling doesn''t look way off though. Won''t be be able to work again on this again before a couple of days though', '2012-10-10 02:41:47'),
(9289932, 465, 'mahagr', 'I''m just wondering why not to remove that field from the database instead...?', '2012-10-10 04:42:09'),
(9290190, 243, 'okonomiyaki3000', 'Hmm. It seems this was never picked up before 3.0 and now parts of it are obsolete. ', '2012-10-10 05:06:12'),
(9290237, 472, 'mahagr', 'Using just JRoute doesn''t work. By default it generates URLs without slugs in it. In order to get aliases right, you need to know exactly how to do that -- including ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute() call with ''id:slug'' format in the parameters.\r<br>\r<br>Most people do not know how to do that as there''s no documentation on it. And the rest of us have just copied the code from Joomla. But I''ve observed some cases when alias doesn''t get added to the article name even if it should -- in other sites the same code is working.', '2012-10-10 05:11:05'),
(9293906, 490, 'shumisha', 'Follow up: had a quick look, styling changes don''t look so simple to me, so if anyone can step in, that''s more likely to bring this fix to completion. Thanks\r<br>', '2012-10-10 08:36:39'),
(9301778, 472, 'phproberto', '@mahagr \r<br>\r<br>ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute() function receives article id and category id as parameters:\r<br>\r<br>    public static function getArticleRoute($id, $catid = 0, $language = 0)\r<br>\r<br>Not so hard to understand. But even if you do something:\r<br>\r<br>    JRoute::_(''index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=22'');\r<br>\r<br>It still generates an ugly URL like "component/content/article?id=22" that works perfectly.\r<br>\r<br>Receiving only the article id like:\r<br>\r<br>    require_once JPATH_SITE.''/components/com_content/helpers/route.php'';\r<br>    JRoute::_(ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute(22));\r<br>\r<br>Can generate the correct SEF URL that works. \r<br>\r<br>Changing that SEF URL is what this patch checks and should not be allowed if you don''t define a custom redirection.\r<br>\r<br>@juliopontes \r<br>\r<br>Applying the current patch fails (another missing ";" ). You should check the patch before commiting.\r<br>\r<br>Also you fixed a few errors but you reintroduced standard validation errors :( This is going to be ethernal if you don''t setup codeSniffer.\r<br>\r<br>Do you want me to make a pull request into your commit to fix remaining issues?\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>', '2012-10-10 12:59:57'),
(9306418, 472, 'juliopontes', '@phproberto yep, please help me.', '2012-10-10 15:07:42'),
(9322623, 494, 'dextercowley', 'Closing. This was an example for a Git tutorial on the wiki. ', '2012-10-10 22:48:48'),
(9325738, 475, 'youjoomla', 'here is the fix \r<br>\r<br>if (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'') { \r<br>(function($) { \r<br>       $(document).ready(function(){\r<br>        $(''.carousel'').each(function(index, element) {\r<br>                $(this)[index].slide = null;\r<br>               });\r<br>         });\r<br> })(jQuery);\r<br>}\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>we can also check for existence of mootools first before doing this like\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>if (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'' && typeof MooTools != ''undefined'' )  { \r<br>// both present , kill jquery slide for carousel class\r<br>(function($) { \r<br>       $(document).ready(function(){\r<br>        $(''.carousel'').each(function(index, element) {\r<br>                $(this)[index].slide = null;\r<br>               });\r<br>         });\r<br> })(jQuery);\r<br>}\r<br>\r<br>this fix is suggested by jq bug squad \r<br>http://bugs.jqueryui.com/ticket/4168\r<br>', '2012-10-11 01:25:31'),
(9329313, 448, 'Chraneco', 'This was merged, so I''m closing it.', '2012-10-11 05:51:57'),
(9335168, 475, 'judgestone', 'Worked a treat, thank you youjoomla.', '2012-10-11 10:23:11');
